Hard Q1 — SAP Purchase Order Register 80 rows
This is a Purchase Order register exported from SAP MM. Paste it in Excel and complete all tasks:

Formatting Tasks:
1. Make Row 1 (header) Bold + Background color Dark Blue + Font color White
2. Format PO Amount column as Accounting format with ₹ symbol and 2 decimals
3. Format Order Date column as DD-MM-YYYY
4. Apply borders to entire data range (all cells)
5. Wrap text in the Vendor Name column
6. Use Format Painter to copy header formatting to a summary row you create below data

Conditional Formatting Tasks:
7. Delivery Status = Delayed → Orange fill on entire row (custom formula: =$I2="Delayed")
8. Delivery Status = Pending → Yellow fill on entire row
9. Delivery Status = Delivered → Green fill on entire row
10. Payment Status = Overdue → Red font on entire row
11. PO Amount above 2,00,000 → Bold Red font on PO Amount column
12. Apply Color Scale on PO Amount column (Green=high, Red=low)
13. Apply Data Bars on Qty column
14. Top 10% rule on PO Amount — what color does Excel apply by default? Write answer below data.

Fill Series Task:
15. Add a column A called "Sr No" — use Fill Series to number all 80 rows automatically


ANSWER :

1. Make Row 1 (header) Bold + Background color Dark Blue + Font color White
